  "Sanction Details" : "ORDER OF CENSURE ISSUED BY STIPULATION, REPLACING ORDER OF CENSURE ISSUED 5/24/85 AS PREVIOUSLY REPORTED. FILE NO. X-2152(L).",
  "Broker Comment" : " BEFORE THE COMMISSIONER OF SECURITIES STATE OF WISCONSIN IN THE MATTER OF WARREN J. BERG, RESPONDENT ORDER RESCINDING CONSENT ORDER OF CENSURE FILED NO. X-2152(L) WHEREAS IT HAS BEEN BROUGHT TO THE ATTENTION OF THE COMMISSIONER OF SECURITIES THAT A CONSENT ORDER OF CENSURE ENTERED MAY 24, 1985 WAS IN ERROR AND IS HEREBY WITHDRAWN AND THE ATTACHED CONSENT ORDER OF CENSURE IS HEREBY SUBSTITUTED AND MADE EFFECTIVE NUNC PRO TUNC ON MAY 26, 1985. THIS ORDER OF CENSURE REPLACES THE ORDER OF CENSURE ISSUED ON MAY 24, 1985. THE EARLIER ORDER CONTAINED LANGUAGE NOT INTENDED BY THE PARTIES TO HAVE BEEN USED. THE ERROR WAS APPARENTLY THAT OF THE ABOVE OFFICE. THE EARLIER STIPULATION FOR CONSENT ORDER OF CENSURE ALLEGES ON OR ABOUT FEBRUARY 10, 1985, BERG PUBLISHED A NEWSPAPER ADVERTISEMENT IN THE GREEN BAY PRESS GAZETTE DESCRIBING THE PAST AVERAGE ANNUAL RETURN OF A BOND TIMING PROGRAM. THE ADVERTISING HAS NEVER BEEN FILED WITH THE OFFICE OF THE WISCONSIN COMMISSIONER OF SECURITIES. THE PUBLICATION OF THE ADVERTISING BY BERG CONSTITUTES UNDER THE CIRCUMSTANCES A VIOLATION BY BURG OF SECS. 551.53(1) (INTRO.) AND (B), WIS. STATS., AND A CAUSE FOR THE CENSURE OF BERG PURSUANT TO SECS. 551-34(1) (INTRO.) AND (B), WISC. STATS.; WHEREAS THE RESPONDENT WISHING TO OBTAIN DISPOSTION HAS DETERMINED NOT TO CONTEST THE ISSUANCE OF AN ORDER IT IS THEREFORE STIPULATED AND AGREED, THE CONSENT ORDER OF CENSURE SHOULD BE ISSUED BY THE COMMISSIONER AGAINST THE RESPONDENT; THE RESPONDENT HEREBY WAIVES HIS RIGHT TO A HEARING. **************************************************************** COPIES OF THE ORDER RESCINDING CONSENT ORDER OF CENSURE AND MOTION TO RESCIND CONSENT ORDER OF CENSURE DATED 5/24/85, AND THE ORIGINAL STIPULATION FOR CONSENT ORDER DATED 5/24/85, ON THE BASIS OF WHICH THE 6/26/85 ORDER OF CENSURE WAS ISSUED ARE ATTACHED) ***SEE FAQ #1*"
}
